      "side": 1,
      "message": "Err right, i meant \nfunc (r HTTPRedirect) Err() error {\n  return errors.New(\"redirect\", r)\n}\n\nIt depends if you like shorthands.  I just happen to like them.\n\nSo that instead of having this in user code:\nif redirect {\n  return nil, errors.New(\"redirect\", common.HTTPRedirect{\"/somewhere\", http.StatusMoved...})\n}\n\nIt\u0027d be\nif redirect {\n  return nil, common.HTTPRedirect{...}.Err()\n}\n\nActually, maybe this makes more sense\n\nif redirect {\n  return nil, common.RedirectError(\"/somewhere\", http.Status...)\n}",
